      <title>Review of targets for the sustainable development goals: The science perspective</title>
      <link>http://knowledge.cta.int/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Review-of-targets-for-the-sustainable-development-goals-The-science-perspective</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This report is an independent scientific review of the 17 Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) and 169 targets, as submitted to the UN General Assembly by the UN Open Working Group (OWG). It is a unique resource for negotiators, technical support teams and other actors engaged in defining a universal, integrated and transformational set of global goals and targets for sustainable development and the political declaration on the post-2015 development agenda. In particular, it is a resource for those carrying out technical reviews of the targets in preparation for their adoption and translation at the national level. With more than 40 contributing authors from 21 countries, the report brings together a wide range of scientific expertise across the natural and social sciences. (ICSU, 13/02/2015)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <author>francis@cta.int (Engelhard Rutger )</author>
      <guid>http://knowledge.cta.int/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Review-of-targets-for-the-sustainable-development-goals-The-science-perspective</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2015 16:53:13 +0000</pubDate>
